history.text: Seen any good movies lately?
Oh yeah. I watched La La Land again the other night. Have you seen it?
I have seen the ads for that, it looks great!
What did you think

It's really good! Damien Chazelle directed it, and he's one of my favorite directors. Always puts a real jazzy theme in his movies, not to mention Ryan Gosling and Emma Stone doing wonderfully as their characters.
It's really a pretty movie too.
I love Chazelle's work! He is brilliant
And who can pass on a Ryan Gosling movie?
lol
Truth!! And look, I know all that stuff at the Oscar's was wild, but it really is a good movie.
What is the basic plot line? I can't get a good feel for it from the ads
Nevermind the crazy Oscar drama!
lol

Well, the two main characters meet in Los Angeles while their both in a point in their lives where they're trying to make their dreams happen. They kind of bond over jazz, and fall in love in an extraordinary fashion.
Wow! The timing sounds amazing! Two people chasing the same dream not only meet but fall in love!
Did they perform together?
They do! It's a romcom/musical so they do a lot of candid singing together, but in the plot of the movie they never performed on stage with each other.
Wasn't a let down to not see them perform together?
Yeah, it ended up being a pretty bitter-sweet thing. No spoilers though!
Ok, you are keeping me intrigued...
Did it win any awards?
I'm not sure off of the top of my head, you'd have to look it  up, but it definitely deserved one in my eyes!
The Oscars don't always get it right in my opinion. If it were up to you, what award(s) would you give it?
Hmmm
Probably best visual effects!
It was REALLY beautiful!
Ok, ok, you have me completely sold! I'm going to check it out this weekend!

uid1response.feedback: I was not familiar with this movie before this conversation. This discussion has made me very interested in going to see it.
